CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776276672
OL,3,CLabour faces losing half of Birmingham
OL,4,Cseats amid Reform surge, poll reveals
OL,6,FAn individual party needs 51 seats to
OL,7,Ftake control of Birmingham City
OL,8,FCouncil, so the only two parties
OL,9,Fcapable of making up the numbers
OL,10,Fwithout additional support are the
OL,11,FConservatives and Reform UK.
OL,13,FIt marks a significant shift from
OL,14,F2022, when Labour held 65 seats,
OL,15,Fcompared to 22 for the Conservatives,
OL,16,F12 for the Liberal Democrats and just
OL,17,F2 for the Greens.
OL,19,FPolitical Reporter Lewis Warner
OL,20,Fexplains the poll
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
