SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1776276672
OL,3,CLabour faces losing half of Birmingham
OL,4,Cseats amid Reform surge, poll reveals
OL,6,FLabour believes the largest party
OL,7,Fshould have the first chance at
OL,8,Fforming an administration, and would
OL,9,Flikely look to the Liberal Democrats
OL,10,Fand Greens as potential partners.
OL,12,FBut on these figures, even that
OL,13,Fcombination would fall short of the 51
OL,14,Fseats needed for a majority.
OL,16,FSome Liberal Democrats have also
OL,17,Fprivately voiced concerns about being
OL,18,Fseen to prop up another Labour-led
OL,19,Fadministration.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/10
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
